  "body": "# submission name:\r\n<!-- the directory name of your submission -->\r\n<!-- please make sure it matches exactly -->\r\nqzs3_tile_delta_r147\r\n\r\n# upload zipped `archive.zip`\r\n<!-- do not check it in the code (it's already ignored in .gitignore) -->\r\n<!-- you can use the upload file feature (drag and drop), make sure curl -L works -->\r\n[archive.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/27314022/archive.zip)\r\n\r\n# report.txt\r\n<!-- do not check it in the code (it's already ignored in .gitignore) -->\r\n<!-- copy the report.txt content here -->\r\n```\r\n=== Evaluation config ===\r\n  batch_size: 16\r\n  device: cuda\r\n  num_threads: 2\r\n  prefetch_queue_depth: 4\r\n  report: submissions/qzs3_tile_delta_r147/report.txt\r\n  seed: 1234\r\n  submission_dir: submissions/qzs3_tile_delta_r147\r\n  uncompressed_dir: /home/neely/dev/comma_video_compression_challenge/videos\r\n  video_names_file: /home/neely/dev/comma_video_compression_challenge/public_test_video_names.txt\r\n=== Evaluation results over 600 samples ===\r\n  Average PoseNet Distortion: 0.00049314\r\n  Average SegNet Distortion: 0.00060631\r\n  Submission file size: 276,551 bytes\r\n  Original uncompressed size: 37,545,489 bytes\r\n  Compression Rate: 0.00736576\r\n  Final score: 100*segnet_dist + √(10*posenet_dist) + 25*rate = 0.31\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n# does your submission require gpu for evaluation (inflation)?\r\n<!-- yes|no -->\r\n<!-- this only applies to inflation, you can use gpu for compression but not require gpu for evaluation -->\r\nyes\r\n\r\n# did you include the compression script? and want it to be merged?\r\n<!-- yes|no -->\r\nno\r\n\r\n# additional comments\r\nQZS3-style neural renderer submission with compact packed payload parsing and sparse evaluator-space tile delta corrections. \r\n\r\n<!-- anything else you want to share -->\r\n<!-- describe your solution -->\r\n",
